50|$|Initially, {{the draft}} succeeded in {{reducing}} the value of <b>signing</b> <b>bonuses.</b> In 1964, {{a year before the}} first draft, University of Wisconsin outfielder Rick Reichardt was given a record bonus of $205,000 ($ today) by the Los Angeles Angels. Without competition from other clubs, the Athletics were able to sign Rick Monday for a bonus of only $104,000. It would take until 1979 for a drafted player to receive a bonus higher than Reichardt's.|$|R
